<DIV><BR><FONT FACE=Arial><FONT COLOR=black SIZE=3>While at The Hartford website, I found this job and thought that you might find it interesting.</FONT><BR><BR>Infrastructure Security Engineer-0805861<BR><BR><B>Job Description</B><BR><DIV><B><P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px">WHY JOIN THE HARTFORD? </P></B><P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px">&nbsp;</P><P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px">As a global leader in insurance, asset management and financial service products, we offer professionals every possibility for growth. And whether we're helping customers or building careers, we're experts at creating the kind of advantages that help people reach their goals. A Fortune 100 company. </P><B><P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px">&nbsp;</P><P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px">THE RESPONSIBILITIES OF THE POSITION?</P></B></DIV><DIV>&nbsp;</DIV><DIV>Candidate will be responsible for:</DIV><DIV>·&nbsp;Managing project and service request fulfillment&nbsp;for designing security based solutions that meet business needs,&nbsp;least based privilege access and role based access control (RBAC) provisioning.</DIV><DIV>·&nbsp;Interfacing with various constituents such as systems developers, end-users, architects and technical peers to drive requirements clarity and solution implementation.</DIV><DIV>·&nbsp;Designing and executing security work in support of off-shore engagements.</DIV><DIV>·&nbsp;Documenting all work executed including&nbsp;designs, support and training docs, and service delivery details. </DIV><DIV>·&nbsp;Understanding the entire lifecycle of identity and entitlements as they relate to access, policy and regulatory requirements.</DIV><DIV>·&nbsp;Defining and implementing the proper methods of access&nbsp;by consulting with users and business representatives. </DIV><BR><BR><B>Qualifications</B><BR><DIV><B><P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px">WHAT QUALIFICATIONS ARE WE LOOKING FOR?</P><P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px">&nbsp;</P></B></DIV><DIV>Required Competencies/Skill Set:</DIV><DIV>·&nbsp;Candidate should possess solid understanding of identity and access management principles.</DIV><DIV>·&nbsp;A deep understanding of the security models within Active Directory is required, and a general focus on security is a plus.</DIV><DIV>·&nbsp;Experience with the design, implementation and management of Active Directory security components such as GPO management, NTFS and Share permissions are required.&nbsp; An understanding of AD trust relationships and impacts for identity as well as local and domain security accounts and boundaries.</DIV><DIV>·&nbsp;Experience with operating in a least based privilege and role based access control (RBAC) environment. </DIV><DIV>·&nbsp;The ability to drive definition in an ambiguous environment is required.</DIV><DIV>·&nbsp;The ability to manage multiple tasks and competing priorities.</DIV><DIV>·&nbsp;Candidate must posses effective time management and organizational skills.</DIV><DIV>·&nbsp;Candidate should demonstrate capabilities in gathering and analyzing technical requirements.</DIV><DIV>·&nbsp;Candidate&nbsp;must be able to effectively work and exhibit strong customer focus with all levels of business and information technology.</DIV><DIV>·&nbsp;Candidate should also be skilled in verbal and written communication.</DIV><DIV>·&nbsp;Candidate should have experience and a demonstrated ability to deliver security designs within the context of thin computing solutions (Citrix and VMWare).</DIV><DIV>·&nbsp;Candidate should possess a solid foundation of 2-5 years experience in Information Technology Security</DIV><DIV>·&nbsp;Ability to script and/or UNIX experience a plus.</DIV><DIV>·&nbsp;Prior experience working in a complex, large scale environment is a plus.</DIV><DIV><B><P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px">&nbsp;</P><P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px">WHAT IS THE COMPENSATION OPPORTUNITY? </P></B>